<br>
As with any group of people things change - people come and go.  People get married.  People get Mad.  People get Uber LOOTZ!<br>
<br>
While it disapontes me that several people have left the guild recently due to whatever reason.  We need to come together and be stronger as a whole.<br>
<br>
Not to belittle anybody nor to reduce them in any way, but weather they or we have identified that they don't fit or don't belong or don't get along or whatever then a correct decision has been made.  Getting rid of a &quot;weak link&quot; can only make the whole stronger.<br>
<br>
I will miss Salvatt and Cornwallis very much - they are friends and will remain that way.  <br>
<br>
We've also gotten some new and strong links in our chain.  Jook, Xaerec, Mallor, Unidin, Ezrel and others that I can't think of their name at this time (I'm sorry, I'm terrible with names.)<br>
<br>
Personally, KoV is my home.  It's the only real guild I've ever been in.  I was there when it started, and I'm going to be there when it disbands (IF EVER)  I've had my problems, as you know, and to overcome them can only make you stronger.<br>
<br>
If you do have a problem, talk about it in a respectful and non-public way.  Any of the officers are very approachable.  I've had long conversations with Bado, Riz, Tamz, Kit, Lang, Nobody as officers, current or otherwise.  ALL of them have been approachable and have offered constructive criticism or good suggestions as to how to resolve issues.  Being an officer in the past, I know what it's like to mediate issues - deal with pissed off members.  It's not easy.  HOWEVER, they will all do it.  You all must think that I'm going on a tangent - I'm not.  My point is that if you have a problem, don't let it fester, confront it - over power it and KILL it like a nasty ORC!<br>
That will make you stronger as well as make the guild stronger as a whole.<br>
<br>
In conclusion, Be mad about people leaving, be sad about people leaving.  Then do whatever it takes to make sure that nobody else leaves.  KoV has a GOOD reputation, I wear my guild tag proudly.  I've been told many times that KoV is a great guild by people I've never met.  <br>
<br>
Amino Et Fide, Knights of Valor!!!!<br>
<br>
<br>
Bascomb Bramblebane  44th Level Druid<br>
Proud member of the Knights of Valor<br>
Guardian of truth and all things with Hairy Feet.<br>
